The paper deals with the design of polar codes for wireless communication channels, which falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and communication (cs.COMM). The focus on slow fading channels and the proposed diversity interleaver and diversity polar code designs suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of systems and control (cs.SY) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the evaluation of the proposed designs through simulations may also make the paper relevant to the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
